ou&#39;re likely to choose to implement? why? and im curious how many man-hours you would expect such a feature to take? &#40;not coding a whole new set of options for an alternate menu, but simply merging a secondary .reg file before the alternate menu is displayed, and un-merging it after it closes&#41;</span></span></span><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"></span></span><br /><span style="color:#323d4f;"><span style="font-family:Lucida Grande, Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;">and you couldn&#39;t just create a copy of all the registry settings with a suffix _2 and use them for the alternate menu?</span></span></span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Sun Apr 07, 2013 9:48 am</p><hr />
