<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=485&amp;p=2515#p2515"><![CDATA[
The thing is the real work happens inside the Explorer process. So:<br />* It will be very hard to keep track of two start menus inside the same process. They will have to work in isolation and have their own settings in the registry<br />* Killing the start menu process accomplishes nothing. It will not exit the start menu. You will have to also kill Explorer<br /><br />As for Win+X, it already works that way, you just have to right-click in the corner.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sun Apr 07, 2013 8:55 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
